We argue the growing numbers of isolated millisecond pulsars\nobserved in globular clusters may have formed, at least in part, through this\nmechanism. In the case of significant mass growth, some of these neutron stars\nmay collapse to form low-mass ($\\lesssim3\\,M_{\\odot}$) black holes.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 14 Apr 2022 18:00:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 27 Jun 2022 18:06:24 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-07-27"}
