ty in the range of [Fe/H] ~ -2.0 to -2.5. Both stars\nare bright (V=12.5 and 13.3, respectively). We urge high-dispersion\nspectroscopic follow-up to determine detailed atmospheric parameters and\nchemical compositions, and to monitor radial velocities.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 14 Apr 2022 19:55:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-04-18"}
